Succinct summary of parsnip object

type_sum.model_spec.Rd

type_sum controls how objects are shown when inside tibble columns.

# S3 method for model_spec
type_sum(x)

# S3 method for model_fit
type_sum(x)

Arguments

x

A model_spec or model_fit object to summarise.

Value

A character value.

Details

For model_spec objects, the summary is "spec[?]" or "spec[+]". The former indicates that either the model mode has not been declared or that the specification has varying() parameters. Otherwise, the latter is shown.

For fitted models, either "fit[x]" or "fit[+]" are used where the "x" implies that the model fit failed in some way.
